column5: Great start on Cedar Lake yesterday.Walleye day with a man and wife team for 4 days.Fantastic start.Walleyes are on the feed bag.Burned through 6 or 7 dozen minnows by noon.It was a drop and catch day.Lor if eaters few a few nice ones.Got into couple of spots holding 10-11" perch to and they aren't shy about biting either.Got up to 29c yesterday and steady 40+ km winds from the south.The terrova had to work hard all day.Did head back to camp for more minnows and fished around there a bit but we had a early day. Raining today and seems all day so my guests have me day off.Still windy also so wilk go again tomorrow.
Congrats, sounds like a great day on the water. Thanks for the report

Tom yesterday was my last day with my guests Dave and Caroline.Been a great week and although windy the weather was awesome except for Monday which had storms and heavy rain.Ended our lthey catching well over 100 plus walleyes according to the 10 doz plus minnows we brought along.Found some very shallow walleyes in 4 spots.Depth varied from 8-15 ft and super aggressive.Average size was 18-23" for the day which was a bonus.Few pike and bass mixed in plus some beautifull large perch.Today tgey are flying into Zizania for a daily flyout with Clarks.Hopefully I'll be able to make a report from Eagle Lake as ill be out there today.
Heading up Saturday. Are the crappies going?
Unfortunately there not. Catch some but tough .they are spread out and not schooled up.
Keep that bite going as I will be at press lake north of Ignace Friday afternoon,doing a week solo.

Bite is strong.Pounded them today with my wife.8 keepers in 8 minutes.lol.Used up all our freebie minnows to tgen went for some casting action which was exciting .How was the woman river.Never heard from you.
